observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
1. Create an Inventory Committee of at least three (3) or more responsible officials to include always the Property Officer and a representative from Accounting Office;
2. Instruct and supervise the conduct of physical inventory count of all properties of the Municipality with a witness of a representative from the Office of the Auditor;
3. Require the Municipal Treasurer to maintain property ledger cards and reconcile with the report of the Municipal Accountant; and
4. Prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) duly signed by the committee members to the Office of the Auditor.

Recommendations:
a. Strictly comply with the provisions of the COA Circular No. 2013-004 date January 30, 2013 to enhance transparency on its operation and project implementation;
b. Furnish the Audit Team the necessary information within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/project/activities and post signboard and/or public notices in the project site for the timely validation.

